<subSubSection pageId="5" pageNumber="6" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="5.[189,310,1917,1943]" box="[189,310,1917,1943]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">
<heading bold="true" box="[189,310,1917,1943]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" reason="3">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,310,1917,1943]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">Diagnosis</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="5.[189,1398,1964,2027]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">
This species resembles the modern genus 
<taxonomicName authority="Van Duzee, 1892" authorityName="Van Duzee" authorityYear="1892" box="[689,1070,1964,1991]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Xestocephalus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[689,858,1964,1990]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">Xestocephalus</emphasis>
Van Duzee, 
<quantity box="[1011,1070,1964,1990]" metricMagnitude="1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.80568" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" unit="in" value="1892.0">1892</quantity>
</taxonomicName>
in the structure of the head and in the leg chaetotaxy but differs in having the head wider than the pronotum, the crown more
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="6" pageNumber="7" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="6.[189,1399,267,329]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">strongly depressed, the forewing elongate, and the front femur lacking an enlarged ventral seta near the midlength.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection box="[189,1078,369,443]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="6.[189,324,369,395]" box="[189,324,369,395]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">
<heading bold="true" box="[189,324,369,395]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" reason="3">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,324,369,395]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">Etymology</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="6.[189,1078,416,443]" box="[189,1078,416,443]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">
The species name refers to the Baltic region, where the 
<typeStatus box="[841,944,416,442]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">holotype</typeStatus>
originated.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
